260
00:14:07,496 --> 00:14:08,720
Scott: It's like an advertising company.

261
00:14:09,380 --> 00:14:12,920
Scott: And another company, which is a company you actually know.

262
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:13,598
Scott: Harmony Gold?

263
00:14:14,602 --> 00:14:15,689
Scott: No, not Harmony Gold.

264
00:14:16,294 --> 00:14:17,200
Scott: Tatsunoko Productions.

265
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,096
Rym: Yes, yes, yes.

266
00:14:18,380 --> 00:14:22,140
Scott: So, those three companies in Japan basically got together to make Macross.

267
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:40,890
Scott: Tatsunoko, on its own, without consulting Big West or Studio Neue, licensed Macross and other stuff to this company in the U.S Harmony Gold, which is like this very strange company.

268
00:14:41,372 --> 00:14:43,097
Scott: It's like such a Hollywood story.

269
00:14:43,117 --> 00:14:46,571
Scott: It's like a real estate company, but they also do some Hollywood stuff.

270
00:14:46,651 --> 00:14:48,440
Scott: They actually made like a movie recently.

271
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:54,420
Scott: It's like a rich dude, but he's not like billionaire rich, but he's still mega real estate Hollywood rich.

272
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:58,268
Scott: You know, it's like a family-run business, right?

273
00:14:58,328 --> 00:15:02,800
Scott: And somehow they got this deal, and there were several lawsuits.

274
00:15:03,381 --> 00:15:17,240
Scott: And when the lawsuits, you know, also involved things like Transformers, because obviously, you know, in the Transformers G1, you had what's-his-name, Firebird, whatever, the guy who's basically the same exact robot as a Valkyrie.

275
00:15:18,041 --> 00:15:19,245
Scott: And there were lawsuits about that.

276
00:15:19,767 --> 00:15:27,120
Scott: And they decided, I guess, and after all these lawsuits, that Harmony Gold still had like the rights to like this limited set of character and designs.

277
00:15:27,481 --> 00:15:32,198
Rym: We'll link to an article, because it's actually not only is it shockingly complex, but also...

278
00:15:32,822 --> 00:15:33,198
Scott: Very complex.

279
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:39,480
Rym: We also like don't know the full details of what happened, because a lot of this was still resolved behind closed doors.

280
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:40,939
Scott: I don't think anyone knows.

281
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:46,797
Rym: But basically, the gist of it was Harmony Gold tried to renew the Macross trademark with Tatsunoko in like the late 90s.

282
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:51,510
Rym: Big West sued, saying that it and not Tatsunoko had rights to that.

283
00:15:52,633 --> 00:16:00,140
Rym: Later, like a decade later or five or six years later, Japanese courts ruled that Tatsunoko had the rights to Macross, including sequel rights.

284
00:16:00,842 --> 00:16:07,260
Rym: But there was some complication that Big West owned the franchise, which included the 41 original designs.

285
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:18,944
Rym: So it was basically fighting over the ownership mostly of merchandising and like the right to the franchise and brand of this stuff, as opposed to the individual show.

286
00:16:18,964 --> 00:16:29,373
Rym: Like imagine if one company had like Scott had the rights to Mickey Mouse as a property for merchandising, but I had the rights to the first 20 things that had Mickey Mouse in it.

287
00:16:29,714 --> 00:16:31,760
Rym: But then some other company owned the rest of Mickey Mouse.

288
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:32,879
Rym: It's one of those situations.

289
00:16:34,081 --> 00:16:34,322
Scott: Right.

290
00:16:34,763 --> 00:16:39,680
Scott: And then you've got a TV show that has Mickey Mouse and Goofy, who's owned by a different person in it.

291
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:45,000
Rym: And then Scott licensed some of the toy stuff to the US, but then I licensed my own stuff to the US.

292
00:16:45,501 --> 00:16:48,429
Scott: And that show that has all these different things in.

293
00:16:48,469 --> 00:16:52,560
Scott: it is called FUBAR, and someone else owns the trademark to FUBAR.

294
00:16:53,121 --> 00:16:54,444
Scott: The title, right?

295
00:16:54,544 --> 00:16:55,987
Scott: It's like Robotech is its own.

296
00:16:56,228 --> 00:17:02,120
Scott: You could own the rights to Robotech conceivably, that trademark, and not own the rights to like the Valkyrie robot.

297
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:03,879
Scott: So what does this actually mean?

298
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:11,117
Scott: So basically what it's meant is that for the longest time, Macross stuff, which is really what we want.

299
00:17:11,137 --> 00:17:12,380
Scott: We want Macross stuff, right?

300
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:17,848
Scott: Everywhere for everybody who was a fan of Macross and has been hard to get right.

301
00:17:18,089 --> 00:17:23,500
Scott: Hard to produce, hard to distribute, because there's just been legal kerfuffles involved.

302
00:17:23,721 --> 00:17:26,329
Scott: If anyone tried to do it right, you tried to license it.

303
00:17:26,348 --> 00:17:29,780
Scott: You'd have to fight with all these people and get, you just don't want to touch it with a hundred foot pole.

304
00:17:30,401 --> 00:17:42,220
Scott: So for the most part, there has been very limited distribution of any Macross related thing outside of Japan, you know, for a very long time.

305
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:44,800
Scott: We've had like the Macross box set that I bought for a fortune.

306
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:45,825
Rym: I remember that.

307
00:17:45,865 --> 00:17:47,780
Rym: I remember how excited we all were about that at RIT.

308
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:51,607
Scott: And you could, you could watch Macross, I think on Amazon prime video.

309
00:17:51,707 --> 00:17:53,832
Scott: And it's like, that's pretty much it, right?

310
00:17:53,872 --> 00:17:57,620
Scott: It's like, you can't, none of this stuff is, is very limited availability.

311
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:10,340
Scott: So what we wanted, what nerds wanted is for basically harmony gold to just lose everything, you know, get this big West garbage out of here, right?

312
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:12,687
Scott: Just studio new, right?

313
00:18:12,707 --> 00:18:16,740
Scott: So, you know, you know, the original, the people who really should just have it, she should just own everything, right?

